value.value: Human RINT1 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 7q22.3 and is approximately 36 kb in length. This allele, which encodes RAD50-interacting protein 1, is involved in both the regulation of vesicle transport and the maintenance of telomeres.
RAD50-interacting protein 1 (792 aa, ~91 kDa) is encoded by the human RINT1 gene. This protein plays a role in both telomere maintenance and vesicle transport.
A question about whether an individual feels or felt that their health is excellent.
An epithelioid hemangioendothelioma that occurs during adulthood.
This gene is involved in nucleotide hydrolysis.

Human NT5E wild-type allele is located within 6q14-q21 and is approximately 46 kb in length. This allele, which encodes 5'-nucleotidase protein, plays a role in nucleoside formation. Mutation of the gene is associated with calcification of joints and arteries.
An epithelioid hemangioendothelioma that occurs during childhood.
5'-nucleotidase (574 aa, ~63 kDa) is encoded by the human NT5E gene. This protein is involved in the conversion of nucleotides to nucleosides.
Inability to effectively digest or absorb the components of breast milk substitutes. Symptoms may include emesis, abdominal distension or diarrhea.
Langerhans cell histiocytosis that occurs during adulthood.

An age group comprised of infants delivered after full 37 weeks gestation whose 5 minute Apgar score was above 7, has no major congenital anomalies and was discharged home with mother without any additional diagnoses except for physiologic hyperbilirubinemia.
An age group comprised of healthy newborns whose only diagnoses are those related to prematurity.
Breast adenocarcinoma that does not respond to hormone therapy.
Prostate carcinoma that does not respond to hormone therapy.
A newborn infant who has weight and/or length at birth more than two standard deviations below the mean for the reference population of the same sex and gestational age.
Birth weight less than 1500 grams.
Birth weight less than 1000 grams.
Birth weight less than 750 grams.
An age group comprised of infants greater than or equal to 34 weeks, 0 days and less than 37 weeks, 0 days gestational age.
An age group comprised of infants less than 28 weeks, 0 days gestational age.
A primary or metastatic malignant neoplasm involving the cardiovascular system.
This gene plays a role in cholesterol metabolism.

Human CYP7B1 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 8q21.3 and is approximately 211 kb in length. This allele, which encodes 25-hydroxycholesterol 7-alpha-hydroxylase enzyme, is involved in cholesterol catabolism. Mutation of the gene is associated with autosomal recessive spastic paraplegia 5A and congenital bile acid synthesis defect 3.
25-hydroxycholesterol 7-alpha-hydroxylase (506 aa, ~58 kDa) is encoded by the human CYP7B1 gene. This protein plays a role in the conversion of cholesterol into bile acids.
A finding indicating the presence of leukemic cell infiltrates in the brain tissue.
This gene is involved in the DNA damage response.

Human ATAD5 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 17q11.2 and is approximately 64 kb in length. This allele, which encodes ATPase family AAA domain-containing protein 5, plays a role in the cellular response to DNA damage.
An age group comprised of infants greater than or equal to 42 weeks, 0 days gestational age.
ATPase family AAA domain-containing protein 5 (1844 aa, ~208 kDa) is encoded by the human ATAD5 gene. This protein is involved in the DNA damage checkpoint.

label.value: Secondary Central Nervous System Hodgkin Lymphoma

value.value: A Hodgkin lymphoma that has spread to the central nervous system following the initial presentation in another nodal or extranodal site.

label.value: Secondary Central Nervous System Non-Hodgkin Lymphoma

value.value: A non-Hodgkin lymphoma that has spread to the central nervous system following the initial presentation in another nodal or extranodal site.
A Hodgkin lymphoma that arises from the central nervous system.
This gene plays a role in the regulation of both gene expression and embryo morphogenesis.

Human EN1 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 2q14.2 and is approximately 6 kb in length. This allele, which encodes homeobox protein engrailed-1, is involved in both embryonic morphogenesis and transcriptional regulation.
Blockage in the biliary tract caused by a malignant neoplasm.
Homeobox protein engrailed-1 (392 aa, ~40 kDa) is encoded by the human EN1 gene. This protein plays a role in both transcriptional regulation and embryonic development.
The reemergence of a childhood astrocytic tumor after a period of remission.
This gene is involved in transcriptional modulation.

Human HHEX wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 10q23.33 and is approximately 7 kb in length. This allele, which encodes hematopoietically-expressed homeobox protein HHEX, plays a role in transcriptional regulation.
Hematopoietically-expressed homeobox protein HHEX (270 aa, ~30 kDa) is encoded by the human HHEX gene. This protein is involved in the negative regulation of transcription.
A morphologic defect of an organ, part of an organ, or a larger region of the body that results from the extrinsic breakdown of, or an interference with, an originally normal developmental process.

label.value: Untreated Childhood Low Grade Astrocytic Tumor

value.value: A finding of childhood low grade astrocytic tumor that has not been treated.

label.value: Untreated Childhood High Grade Astrocytic Tumor

value.value: A finding of childhood high grade astrocytic tumor that has not been treated.
A fibrillary astrocytoma that occurs during childhood.
A gemistocytic astrocytoma that occurs during childhood.
Thin rings of enhancement visible in MRI that are clustered together around breast ducts in an area that is neither a mass nor a foci.
